<div class="grid__col--12 page-section form" id="form">
    <div class="content">
        <h1>Form Elements</h1>
        <p class="intro">Forms should be a maximum of 650px wide to prevent inputs being too long. Only include form fields that are absolutely necessary in order to try and reduce drop offs during completion.</p>
        <hr />
        <h2>Input Elements</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col col1">
                    <label for="email">Email Address:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <input name="email" type="text" id="email" class="fuzzy">
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Required fields should display the asterisk next to the label using the class <code>.star</code> on a <code>span</code> tag.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col colhalf">
                    <label for="firstname">First Name:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <input name="firstname" type="text" id="firstname" class="fuzzy">
                </div>
                <div class="col colhalf">
                    <label for="lastname">Last Name:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <input name="lastname" type="text" id="lastname" class="fuzzy">
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Inputs can appear side by side if they are related e.g. first and last name.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <input class="fuzzy input-with-button" id="postcode" name="postcode" placeholder="Enter a postcode"> <input class="button" type="submit" value="Find Shop">
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Inputs with a button should have both items on one line, until mobile sizes where they can break to two lines.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Textarea</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col col1 textarea">
                    <label for="message">Your Message:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <textarea name="message" id="message" class="fuzzy"></textarea>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Textareas should always be displayed at 100% width of the form, and default to 80px height, but allow for user resizing.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Labels</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col col1">
                    <div id="Content__telephoneDiv" class="fieldcolumn">
                        <label for="telephone">Phone number:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                        <input name="telephone" type="text" id="telephone" maxlength="50" class="fuzzy">
                    </div>
                    <small class="data-info">Please note this will only be used to update you about orders you have placed with COOK.</small>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Labels should be succinct, short and descriptive (a word or two) so users can quickly scan the form. E.g. Full name NOT Please enter your full name.</p>
            <p class="intro">Labels should always appear on top of the field.</p>
            <p class="intro">Additional notes to help the user complete the form can be added underneath the relevant field. Use <code>small</code> tag with class <code>.data-info</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Error Messages</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="main-error">
                    <p>There were some problems with some of the information you entered. Please check the highlighted sections below and try again.</p>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Every form should have a main error message that explains that there is an error and directs the user to the appropriate field, this should appear at the top of the form.</p>
            <p class="intro">Use class <code>.main-error</code> on a <code>div</code> with child <code>p</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col col1 error">
                    <label for="email">Email Address:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <input name="email" type="text" id="email" maxlength="255" class="fuzzy" value="" autocomplete="off">
                    <p>Email address is a required field.</p>
                </div>
            </form>
            <form>
                <div class="col col1 error">
                    <label for="email">Email Address:<span class="star">*</span></label>
                    <input name="email" type="text" id="email" maxlength="255" class="fuzzy" value="" autocomplete="off">
                    <p>Email address should be in the format example@email.com.</p>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br />
            <p class="intro">Use clear and polite language, wording should be conversational and helpful.</p>
            <p class="intro">Error messages should clearly define what the problem was, why it happened, and what to do about it.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Selects</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="col col1">
                    <label>Shop:</label>
                    <div class="styled-select fit-box">
                        <select name="pickupshop" id="pickupshop">
                            <option selected="selected" value="">-- Please select --</option>
                            <option value="33">East Grinstead</option>
                            <option value="29">Haywards Heath</option>
                            <option value="42">Lewes</option>
                            <option value="15">Tonbridge</option>
                            <option value="16">Tunbridge Wells</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br /><br />
            <p class="intro">Selects should have the label above it and should not have a 'Please select' option as the default value. Selects should be consistently styled, on desktops broswers. On mobile and tablet the native interactions should be maintained.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Checkboxes</h2>
        <div class="style__box">
            <form>
                <div class="checkbox">
                    <label class="mobile-checkbox-styling marketing-optin">
                        <input name="emailsub" type="checkbox" id="emailsub">
                        <span class="checkbox-label"><span>Emails - Yes please, send me tasty emails</span> Sign up for email and get news, special offers and fun stuff straight to your inbox. </span>
                    </label>
                </div>
            </form>
            <form>
                <div class="checkbox">
                    <label class="mobile-checkbox-styling">
                        <input name="tandc" type="checkbox" id="tandc" class="styled-checkbox">
